    "section_faq_gGTfJc": {
      "type": "section-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "text_TgwwXe": {
          "type": "text",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "How will my items be priced?",
            "content": "<p><a href=\"/pages/condition-and-pricing\" title=\"Condition and Pricing Criteria\">See Our Conditions & Pricing Page</a></p>"
          }
        },
        "text_nHfreX": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Frequently asked question",
            "content": "<p>Share details about your shipping policies, item returns, or customer service.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_bqJ9w6": {
          "type": "text",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is TTE's Buyout Program?",
            "content": "<p><strong>FROM HORSEBACK TO CASHBACK!<br/><br/></strong>No need to wait to get paid for your items to sell!<br/>The Tried Equestrian now offers quick cash or store credit for select tack and apparel in excellent condition.<br/><br/><strong>BUYOUT PROCESS</strong></p><p>For items that meet The Tried Equestrian's Buyout guidelines, a Buyout Proposal is emailed, outlining each piece we want to purchase and a buyout total in cash or Store Credit. Any items we cannot purchase would fall into our traditional consignment program. If the proposal is accepted, we will send the payment within one week.</p><p><strong><br/>BUYOUT PAYMENT STRUCTURE</strong></p><p>Choose between Store Credit, PayPal or mailed check.</p><ul><li>Check or PayPal payout - consignor receives 25% of TTE price</li><li>Store credit payout - consignor receives 40% of TTE price</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "text_cWyTkk": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How many items should I consign at a time?",
            "content": "<p>We ask for a minimum of 5 acceptable items and a minimum of $500 of retail value total. </p>"
          }
        },
        "text_bqk7tX": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is your consignment aggreement?",
            "content": "<p><a href=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1735/6525/files/2024_Consignment_Agreement.pdf?v=1708016300\" title=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1735/6525/files/2024_Consignment_Agreement.pdf?v=1708016300\">See our Consignment Agreement Here</a></p>"
          }
        },
        "text_C4bAYf": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What happens to not accepted items or items that aren't selling?",
            "content": "<p>The Tried Equestrian reserves the right to decline any item for resale at our sole discretion. All items must be in <em>very good</em> to <em>new with tags</em> condition (as evaluated by our team).</p><p>If an item is deemed unsuitable for resale, we’ll refer to the preferences outlined in your consignment agreement to determine next steps:</p><ul><li>If you’ve selected to have unaccepted items returned, we’ll send you an invoice for return shipping and any packing materials used. We always charge the lowest available market rates.</li></ul><p></p><ul><li>If you’ve chosen donation or do not pay the return shipping invoice, all rights to the item are forfeited, and it will be handled at our discretion—this may include donation, recycling, or resale.</li></ul><p><strong>Discounting Policy</strong></p><p>All items are consigned for a minimum of 180 days (six months). To help ensure a successful sale, The Tried Equestrian reserves the right to apply the following price reductions:</p><ol><li>20 % at any time for sitewide or promotional incentives<br/></li><li>30% off original listing price after 90 days<br/></li><li>40% off after 120 days<br/></li><li>50% off after 150 days<br/></li><li>Up to 70% after 180 days to any price we believe will help the item sell<br/></li></ol><p>Our goal is to strike the right balance between value and visibility to get your items sold.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_YjmzPh": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What brands do you accept?",
            "content": "<p>See our list of accepted brands <a href=\"https://www.triedequestrian.com/pages/brands-we-currently-accept\" title=\"https://www.triedequestrian.com/pages/brands-we-currently-accept\">here</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_HKhRqR": {
          "type": "text",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "What brands do you not accept?",
            "content": "<ul><li>GHM (George Morris) </li><li>Equine Couture Breeches </li><li>Dry clean only show coats</li><li>Cracked or damaged leather</li><li>Plain hunter brow bands</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "text_ibbmrt": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How does payment work and what are the commissions and fees?",
            "content": "<p><strong>What Percent Commission Do You Make?</strong></p><ul><li>Consigned items priced by TE at $19.99 & under are ineligible for consignment and will be returned/disposed of according to Section 2 “Unacceptable Items”</li><li>Consignor will receive 20% of sales revenue for sale of a consigned item priced by TE at $20.00-$49.99</li><li>Consignor will receive 40% of sales revenue for sale of a consigned item priced by TE at $50.00--$99.99</li><li>Consignor will receive 50% of sales revenue for sale of a consigned item priced by TE at $100.00-$249.99</li><li>Consignor will receive 60% of sales revenue for sale of a consigned item priced by TE at $250.00 -$499.99</li><li>Consignor will receive 70% of sales revenue for sale of a consigned item priced by TE at $500.00-$999.99</li><li>Consignor will receive 80% of sales revenue for sale of a consigned item priced by TE at $1000.00 or more.</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Fees</strong></p><ul><li>$20/ shipment processing fee for shipped consignment kits</li><li>All boots not professionally cleaned are subject to a cleaning fee:  </li><li>Items needing dry cleaning or repairs are billed on a case by case basis.</li><li>Shipping Fees - never to exceed 10% of the sale price including excess shipping weight and free shipping to the customer</li></ul><p><strong>How Do You Get Paid? </strong></p><p>At the beginning of the month a check will be sent out with an invoice breakdown. We delay sending payments by one month to accommodate any returns. You are able to check the real-time status of your items in our <a href=\"https://tried-eq.herokuapp.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Consignor Portal\">Consignor Portal</a></p><p>Options to Receive Payment:</p><ul><li><strong>Mailed Check</strong></li><li><strong>PayPal</strong></li><li><strong>TriedEq Store Credit- </strong>Receive 5%-10% more for your items! </li><li><strong>Donate Sales to Charity!</strong></li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "text_T989rg": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "title": "I didn't get the payout I expected.",
            "content": "<p>Resale prices often differ from what items originally cost at retail—and that can come as a surprise. By the time a piece reaches the secondary market, it may have already been discounted by the retailer, which lowers the resale value as well.</p><p>Beyond that, other factors also impact pricing:<br/><br/>• Market demand may have shifted (what was once a must-have may now be out of style)<br/><br/>• Newer versions or updated designs may have been released<br/><br/>• Wear, use, or missing original packaging can affect value<br/><br/>• Similar items may already be listed in abundance, driving prices down</p><p>Our goal is always to price items as competitively as possible to help them sell—while still honoring their value.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
